Short-term interbank rates are expected to remain stable today on Bank Negara Malaysia intervention to absorb excess liquidity from the financial system. The central bank estimated today's surplus at RM30. 400 billion in the conventional system and RM12. 485 billion in Islamic funds. Bank Negara will call for a RM7 billion range maturity auction tender for 2-63 days. The central bank will also call for two repo tenders comprising RM900 million for 30 days and RM400 million for 91 days. At 4pm, Bank Negara will conduct up to RM22. 1 billion in conventional overnight tenders and a RM4. 6 billion Al-Wadiah overnight tender.  â€“ Bernama, April 7, 2014. 